Citation.sAbstract: The densities at T = (288.15, 293.15, 298.15, 303.15, and 308.15) K and sound velocities at T = 298.15 K  have been measured for aqueous solutions of urea, N-methylurea, N,N -dimethylurea, N,N,N N -tetramethylurea,  N-ethylurea, N,N -diethylurea, N-butylurea. From these data the apparent molar volumes, VU  the apparent molar isentropic compressions, KS,U, and the Passynski solvation numbers of solutes have  been determined. The concentration dependencies of the calculated quantities and their limiting values  are discussed in terms of solute solvent and solute solute interactions.
Citation.sTitle: Densimetric and ultrasonic characterization of urea and its derivatives in water
